Importing Ensembl gene annotations and getting entrez ids

This step is important to make sure Ensembl ids are converted to entrez ids, using the biomaRt package, since clusterProfiler works primarily with entrez ids.

db_homo_s <- useMart(biomart = 'ENSEMBL_MART_ENSEMBL', dataset = 'hsapiens_gene_ensembl')

# Function to convert and append Entrez ID to data frames

translator <- function(df_ranked, info2cluster){
  new_df <- df_ranked
  dictionary <- getBM(attributes = c('ensembl_gene_id', 'entrezgene_id'),
                      filters = 'ensembl_gene_id', values = new_df$Gene.ID,
                      mart = db_homo_s, uniqueRows = F, useCache = T)
  
  new_df <- left_join(new_df, dictionary, by = join_by('Gene.ID' == 'ensembl_gene_id'),
                      multiple = 'first') %>% relocate(entrezgene_id, .after = Gene.ID)
  
  colnames(new_df) <- c('ensembl', 'entrez', 'metric')
  
  if (missing(info2cluster)){return(new_df)}
  
  else {
    new_df$group <- info2cluster
    
    return(new_df)}

}

hsGO <- GOSemSim::godata(OrgDb = 'org.Hs.eg.db', keytype = 'ENSEMBL', ont = 'BP')

SCZ_tnf_vs_SCZ_ns <- translator(SCZ_tnf_vs_SCZ_ns, 'vs_SCZ_ns')

GSEA with GO terms or KEGG Pathways

The clusterProfiler package has a function that allows gene-set enrichment analysis between multiple groups at once, called compareCluster. From the results of this function, users can generate a wide range of different plots and retrieve dataframes to create summarized tables, including core-enriched genes and leading edges.

Here, we included all these steps in a single custom-made function called cluster_comparision that was used to retrieve dataframes to generate the Supplementary Tables shown in this work as well as the dotplots figures summarizing our findings.

cluster_comparison <- function(df_ranked_list, name, select_fun = c('gseGO', 'gseKEGG', 'gseDGN', 'gseDO', 'GSEA'), dataset, reversed = FALSE){
  
  set.seed(12345)
  
  # Preparing ranked list to compare cluster function
  
  new_df <- data.frame(df_ranked_list[1])
  cluster_df <- new_df[,2:4]
  
  i <- 2
  
  while (i <= length(df_ranked_list)){
    new_df <- data.frame(df_ranked_list[i])
    new_df <- new_df[,2:4]
    
    cluster_df <- rbind(cluster_df, new_df)
    
    i <- i + 1}
  
  rm(new_df)
  
  # Indicating whether cluster results should be read as it is on in reversed order
  
  if (!is.logical(reversed)){
    stop('Not a logical value! Only TRUE or FALSE values are allowed!')}
  
  else{
    
    if (reversed){cluster_df$metric <- -1 * cluster_df$metric}
    
    else{}}
  
  # Choosing between GO Biological 
  
  options(cluster = snow::makeCluster(spec = 6, 'SOCK'))
  
  if (select_fun == 'gseGO' | select_fun == 'gseKEGG' | select_fun == 'gseMKEGG'){
    
    if (select_fun == 'gseGO'){title_dotplot <- 'GO Biological Process'
    cluster <- compareCluster(entrez | metric ~ group, fun = select_fun,
                              data = cluster_df, ont = 'BP',
                              OrgDb = 'org.Hs.eg.db',
                              minGSSize = 15, maxGSSize = 500, eps = 0,
                              pvalueCutoff = 0.1, pAdjustMethod = 'BH',
                              verbose = F, by = 'fgsea')}
    
    else if (select_fun == 'gseMKEGG'){title_dotplot <- 'KEGG Pathways Modules'
    cluster <- compareCluster(entrez | metric ~ group, fun = select_fun,
                              data = cluster_df, organism = 'hsa', 
                              keyType = 'ncbi-geneid',
                              minGSSize = 15, maxGSSize = 500, eps = 0,
                              pvalueCutoff = 0.1, pAdjustMethod = 'BH',
                              verbose = F, by = 'fgsea')}
    
    else{title_dotplot <- 'KEGG Pathways'
    cluster <- compareCluster(entrez | metric ~ group, fun = select_fun,
                              data = cluster_df, organism = 'hsa', 
                              keyType = 'ncbi-geneid',
                              minGSSize = 15, maxGSSize = 500, eps = 0,
                              pvalueCutoff = 0.1, pAdjustMethod = 'BH',
                              verbose = F, by = 'fgsea')}}
  
  else if (select_fun == 'gseDO' | select_fun == 'gseDGN'){
    
    if (select_fun == 'gseDO'){title_dotplot <- 'Disease Ontology'}
    
    else {title_dotplot <- 'DISGENET'}
    
    cluster <- compareCluster(entrez | metric ~ group, fun = select_fun,
                              data = cluster_df, minGSSize = 10,
                              maxGSSize = 500, eps = 0,
                              pvalueCutoff = 0.1, pAdjustMethod = 'BH',
                              verbose = F, by = 'fgsea')}
  
  else if (select_fun == 'GSEA'){
    
    title_dotplot <- deparse(substitute(dataset))
    
    cluster <- compareCluster(entrez | metric ~ group, fun = select_fun,
                              data = cluster_df, eps = 0, minGSSize = 10,
                              maxGSSize = Inf,
                              pvalueCutoff = 1, pAdjustMethod = 'BH',
                              TERM2GENE = dataset,
                              verbose = F, by = 'fgsea')}
  
  
  else{stopifnot('gseGO', 'gseKEGG', 'gseMKEGG', 'gseDO', 'gseDGN', 'GSEA')}
  
  stopCluster(getOption("cluster"))
  
  cluster <- setReadable(cluster, OrgDb = org.Hs.eg.db, keyType = 'ENTREZID')
  
  cluster@compareClusterResult$Expression[cluster@compareClusterResult$NES > 0] <- 'Up'
  cluster@compareClusterResult$Expression[cluster@compareClusterResult$NES < 0] <- 'Down'
  
  # CREATE RESULTS TABLE
  
  res <- data.frame(cluster@compareClusterResult)

  write.table(res[,c(1,4:length(res)-1)], file = paste0('Compare_cluster_',
                                                        title_dotplot, '_', name,'.csv'), quote = F, sep = '\t', row.names = F)
  
  
  return(cluster)
}

# Running compare cluster for GO Biological process and KEGG Pathways

list_ranked_lists <- list(SCZ_ns, SCZ_tnf, HCP_tnf)

compare_gobp <- cluster_comparison(list_ranked_lists, 'vs_HCP_ns', 'gseGO')
compare_kegg <- cluster_comparison(list_ranked_lists, 'vs_HCP_ns', 'gseKEGG')

# Creating dotplot graphs

dotplot_gsea <- function(cluster, name, title_dotplot, pathways){
  
  # CREATE DOTPLOT
  
  cluster_plot <- cluster
  
  cluster_plot@compareClusterResult$p.adjust <- -log10(cluster_plot@compareClusterResult$p.adjust)
  
  max_p.adjust <- ceiling(max(cluster_plot@compareClusterResult$p.adjust))
  
  divisor <- floor(max_p.adjust / 4)
  
  dot_go <- dotplot(cluster_plot, x = 'Cluster', color = 'p.adjust', showCategory = pathways,
                    split = 'Expression', size = 'GeneRatio', label_format = 40) +  ggtitle(title_dotplot) +
    scale_fill_viridis(name = expression(bold('-log'[10]*' (p-adj)')), option = 'H',
                       limits = c(0, max_p.adjust), breaks = seq(0, max_p.adjust, divisor)) +
    scale_size_continuous(name = 'GeneRatio', limits = c(0, 1), breaks = seq(0.1, 0.7, 0.2), range = c(1,10)) +
    theme(legend.title = element_text(family = 'sans', face = 'bold'),
          title = element_text(family = 'sans', face = 'bold', size = 12, hjust = 0.5),
          axis.text.x = element_text(family = 'sans', face = 'bold', size = 10, angle = 45, hjust = 1, vjust = 1),
          axis.title.x = element_blank(),
          axis.text.y = element_text(family = 'sans', size = 8),
          axis.ticks.length = unit(8, "pt"),
          panel.border = element_rect(color = 'black', fill = NA, linewidth = 1),
          axis.line = element_line(color = 'black', linewidth = 1),
          axis.ticks = element_line(color = 'black', linewidth = 1),
          strip.background = element_rect(color = 'black', fill = 'grey80', linewidth = 1),
          strip.placement = 'outside',
          strip.text = element_text(family = 'sans', face = 'bold', size = 10)) +
    facet_wrap(~fct_rev(Expression)) 
  
  ggsave(paste0('Compare_cluster_', title_dotplot, '_', name, '.pdf'),
         plot = dot_go, width = 200, height = 200, unit = 'mm')

}

plot_gobp <- dotplot_gsea(compare_gobp, 'vs_HCP_ns', 'GO Biological Process', selected_go_terms)
plot_kegg <- dotplot_gsea(compare_kegg, 'vs_HCP_ns', 'KEGG Pathways', selected_kegg)

Running GSEA against the Prater et al (2023) and CellAge datasets

This dataset contains human DLPFC microglial signature from Alzheimers disease patients. Here, we restricted our comparison to the APOE3/APOE3 genotype to prevent any potential effect of APOE4 alleles, since they are the highest risk factor for LOAD.

# Importing and tidying tables from 'Supplementary Data 2' file found in the supplementary material from Prater et al (2023).
# T1 = spreadsheet named "DEG_cluster_to_all"
# T2 = spreadsheet names "DEG_cluster_to_clust1"

prater2023_t1 <- read.table(/FILE_NAME/, sep = '\t', header = T)
prater2023_t2 <- read.table(/FILE_NAME/, sep = '\t', header = T)

prater2023 <- subset(prater2023_t2, prater2023_t2$avg_logFC > 0) %>% dplyr::select(Gene, Cluster)

# Retrieving 'homeostatic' cluster signature

prater_hm_genes <- subset(prater2023_t1, prater2023_t1$avg_logFC > 0 & prater2023_t1$cluster == 1) %>%
  dplyr::select(gene, cluster)
prater_hm_genes$cluster <- 'Homeostatic'
colnames(prater2023) <- c('gene', 'cluster')

# Merging dataframes with signatures from all clusteres

prater2023 <- rbind(prater2023, prater_hm_genes)

dictionary <- getBM(attributes = c('hgnc_symbol', 'entrezgene_id'),
                    filters = 'hgnc_symbol', values = prater2023$gene,
                    mart = db_homo_s, uniqueRows = F, useCache = T)

prater2023 <- left_join(prater2023, dictionary, by = join_by('gene' == 'hgnc_symbol'),
                              multiple = 'first') %>% dplyr::select(cluster, entrezgene_id) %>%
  relocate(entrezgene_id, .after = cluster) %>% na.omit()

colnames(prater2023) <- c('term', 'gene')

Creating Heatmap plots from the above results

heatmap_gsea <- function(cluster, name, title){
  
  cluster_plot <- cluster@compareClusterResult
  
  cluster_plot$NES <- ifelse(cluster_plot$p.adjust < 0.1, cluster_plot$NES, 0)
  
  cluster_plot <- tapply(cluster_plot$NES, cluster_plot[c('group', 'ID')], mean)
  
  heatmap_go <- Heatmap(cluster_plot, col = colorRamp2(c(-2,0,2), hcl_palette = 'Blue-Red 3'),
                        name = 'NES', show_column_dend = F, show_row_dend = F, na_col = 'grey70',
                        rect_gp = gpar(col = 'black', lwd = 1), cluster_rows = F,
                        row_names_side = 'left', show_column_names = T, cluster_columns = F,
                        row_names_gp = gpar(fontfamily = 'sans', fontsize = 10),
                        column_names_gp = gpar(fontfamily = 'sans', fontsize = 10), 
                        column_names_side = 'top',  row_names_centered = F, column_names_centered = F,
                        width = ncol(cluster_plot) * unit(8, 'mm'), height = nrow(cluster_plot) * unit(8, 'mm'),
                        show_heatmap_legend = T)
  
  ggsave(paste0('Compare_cluster_', title, '_', name, '.pdf'),
         plot = grid.grabExpr(draw(heatmap_go)))
  
}

plot_cellage <- heatmap_gsea(compare_cellage, 'vs_HCP_ns', 'CellAge')
plot_prater <- heatmap_gsea(compare_prater, 'vs_HCP_ns', 'prater2023')
